This memorandum, issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., addresses the history of discriminatory housing policies in the United States and outlines the administration's commitment to ending housing discrimination and promoting fair and equal access to housing opportunities for all. The memorandum acknowledges the role of the federal government in perpetuating segregation and discrimination and emphasizes the need to undo historic patterns of discrimination. It directs the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) to examine the effects of recent regulatory actions related to fair housing and take necessary steps to implement the Fair Housing Act's requirements. The memorandum also includes general provisions regarding the implementation of this policy.